<title>GREECE: ROKAS, ALUM OF GREECE TRADE EX-DIV FRIDAY.</title>
<headline>ROKAS, ALUM OF GREECE TRADE EX-DIV FRIDAY.</headline>
<dateline>ATHENS 1997-06-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of Rokas and</p>
<p>Aluminium of Greece are trading ex-dividend Friday.</p>
<p>Their respective 1996 dividends per share -- 75 and 821</p>
<p>drachmas.</p>
<p>Also on Friday, shares of Singular are trading</p>
<p>ex-rights. A total of 1,450,360 rights start trade at 105</p>
<p>drachmas. The daily volatility limit is 8.0 percent. They expire</p>
<p>July 21.</p>
<p>Adjusted starting prices for the above shares will have as</p>
<p>follows, the bourse said:</p>
<p>    Arcadia Rokas	     2,415   drachmas</p>
<p>    Arcadia Rokas  pref     1,975</p>
<p>    Alum of Greece	   17,099</p>
<p>			 pref    18,174</p>
<p>			 pref nv 16,379</p>
<p>    Singular		    3,195</p>
<p>--George Georgiopoulos, Athens Newsroom +301 3311812-4</p>
</text>
